bend-sft-taylor\">{{cite web|last=Taylor|first=Lon|title=Getting History Wrong on the Silver Screen|publisher=Big Bend Now|date=February 26, 2015|url=http://bigbendnow.com/2015/02/the-rambling-boy-62|accessdate=March 16, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150307075949/http://bigbendnow.com/2015/02/the-rambling-boy-62/|archive-date=March 7, 2015|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"brooklyn-daily-burdett\">{{cite news|last=Burdett|first=Winston|title=A Midsummer Night's Dream Returns|newspaper=Brooklyn Daily Eagle|page=6|date=October 5, 1936|url=https://www.newspapers.com/image/52692348/?terms=Midsummer%2BNight's%2BDream|accessdate=February 23, 2016}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"cbsnews-djansezian-shocked\">{{cite web|last=Djansezian|first=Kevork|title=Olivia de Havilland 'shocked and saddened' by sister Joan Fontaine's death|publisher=CBS News|date=December 16, 2013|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/olivia-de-havilland-shocked-and-saddened-by-sister-joan-fontaines-death|accessdate=January 21, 2016}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"cnn-facts\">{{cite news|title=Olivia de Havilland Fast Facts|publisher=CNN|url=http://www.cnn.com/2013/01/21/us/olivia-de-havilland-fast-facts|accessdate=January 21, 2016}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"french-observer\">{{cite news|last=French|first=Philip|title=Screen Legends No. 73|newspaper=The Observer|year=2009}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"getty-galella\">{{cite web|last=Galella|first=Ron|title=Marlene Dietrich's Opening Party|publisher=Getty Images |date=September 9, 1967|url=http://www.gettyimages.com/detail/news-photo/joan-fontaine-and-sister-olivia-de-havilland-during-marlene-news-photo/105274140|accessdate=January 21, 2016}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"golden-globes-olivia\">{{cite web|title=Olivia de Havilland |publisher=Golden Globes|url=http://www.goldenglobes.com/person/olivia-de-havilland|accessdate=April 23, 2016}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"guardian-french\">{{cite news|last=French|first=Philip|title=Philip French's screen legends No. 73: Olivia de Havilland |newspaper=The Guardian|date=October 31, 2009|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2009/dec/22/olivia-de-havilland-screen-legend|accessdate=January 21, 2016}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"hollywood-walk\">{{cite web|title=Olivia de Havilland|publisher=Hollywood Walk of Fame|url=http://www.walkoffame.com/olivia-de-havilland|accessdate=January 23, 2016}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"hr-feinberg-feud\">{{cite web|last=Feinberg|first=Scott|title=Joan Fontaine-Olivia de Havilland Feud: New Details Revealed|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=December 17, 2013|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/race/joan-fontaine-olivia-de-havilland-666087?page=2|accessdate=January 21, 2016}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"huffpost-gitau\">{{cite web|last=Gitau|first=Rosalia|title=Art Therapy for Alzheimer's: I Remember Better When I Paint|work=The Huffington Post|date=May 11, 2010|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/rosalia-gitau/art-therapy-for-alzheimer_b_495914.html|accessdate=March 28, 2016}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"independent-cornwell\">{{cite news|last=Cornwell|first=Rupert|title=Sibling rivalry: Hollywood's oldest feud|newspaper=The Independent|date=May 15, 2008|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/films/features/sibling-rivalry-hollywoods-oldest-feud-828301.html|accessdate=January 21, 2016}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"latimes-mathews\">{{cite news|last=Mathews|first=Jack|title=1939: It was the greatest year in Hollywood history|newspaper=Los Angeles Times|date=January 1, 1989|url=https://articles.latimes.com/1989-01-01/entertainment/ca-223_1_greatest-year|accessdate=March 11, 2016}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"latimes-tartaglione\">{{cite news|last=Tartaglione|first=Nancy|title=Olivia and Oscar|newspaper=Los Angeles Times|date=March 23, 2003|url=https://articles.latimes.com/2003/mar/23/entertainment/ca-q-a23|accessdate=April 9, 2016}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"nation-agee\">{{cite magazine|last=Agee|first=James|title=The Dark Mirror (1946)|magazine=The Nation|issue=19|date=November 9, 1946|page