: The Lives of Danny Kaye |publisher=Simon & Schuster |location=New York |year=2002 |isbn=978-0-7432-4476-3 |ref=harv |url-access=registration |url=https://archive.org/details/unset0000unse_x1y9 }}\n* {{cite book |last=Herman |first=Jan |title=A Talent for Trouble |publisher=G. P. Putnam's Sons |location=New York |year=1995 |isbn=978-0-399-14012-9 |ref=harv |url=https://archive.org/details/talentfortrouble00herm }}\n* {{cite book |last=Higham |first=Charles |title=Sisters: The Story of Olivia de Havilland and Joan Fontaine |publisher=Coward McCann |location=New York |year=1984 |isbn=978-0-698-11268-1 |ref=harv |url=https://archive.org/details/sistersstoryofol00high }}\n* {{cite magazine|last=Jensen |first=Oliver O. |title=Sister Act |magazine=Life |volume=12 |issue=18 |pages=88\u201394 |date=May 4, 1942 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ClAEAAAAMBAJ&printsec=frontcover#v=onepage&q&f=false |accessdate=February 16, 2016 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last=Kass |first=Judith M. |title=Olivia de Havilland |publisher=Pyramid Publications |location=New York |year=1976 |isbn=978-0-515-04175-0 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last=Matzen |first=Robert |title=Errol & Olivia: Ego & Obsession in Golden Era Hollywood |publisher=Paladin Communications |location=Pittsburgh |year=2010 |isbn=978-0-9711685-8-9 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|editor-first1=Paul |editor-last1=McDonald |editor-first2=Emily |editor-last2=Carman |editor-first3=Eric |editor-last3=Hoyt |editor-first4=Philip |editor-last4=Drake |title=Hollywood and the Law |publisher=British Film Institute |location=London |year=2015 |isbn=978-1-84457-478-0 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last=Meyers |first=Jeffrey |title=John Huston: Courage and Art |publisher=Crown Archetype |location=New York |year=2011 |isbn=978-0-307-59069-5 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Reagan |first=Ronald |title=Ronald Reagan: An American Life |publisher=Simon & Schuster |location=New York |year=1990 |isbn=978-0-671-69198-1 |ref=harv |url-access=registration |u